---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Download — Aivyx" description="Download and install Aivyx — privacy-first AI agent for Linux, macOS, and Windows.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>Get <span class="accent">Aivyx</span></h1>
    <p>Up and running in under 5 minutes. Free, open source, MIT licensed.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="steps-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Step-by-Step Installation</h2>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Install Rust</h3>
          <p>Aivyx is written in Rust. If you don't have Rust installed yet, run this one-liner in your terminal:</p>
          <pre><code>curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh</code></pre>
          <p class="hint">Follow the prompts — the defaults are fine. When it finishes, <strong>close and reopen your terminal</strong> so the <code>cargo</code> command becomes available.</p>
          <p class="hint">Already have Rust? Make sure you're on 1.85 or newer: <code>rustup update</code></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Install Aivyx</h3>
          <p>This downloads the source code from GitHub and compiles it on your machine (takes about 1–2 minutes):</p>
          <pre><code>cargo install --git https://github.com/AivyxDev/aivyx.git aivyx-cli</code></pre>
          <p class="hint">The binary is installed to <code>~/.cargo/bin/aivyx</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Make Sure It's in Your PATH</h3>
          <p>If typing <code>aivyx</code> gives "command not found", add cargo's bin folder to your PATH:</p>
          <div class="tab-group">
            <div class="tab-card">
              <h4>Bash</h4>
              <pre><code>echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.cargo/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="tab-card">
              <h4>Zsh</h4>
              <pre><code>echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.cargo/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc</code></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="tab-card">
              <h4>Fish</h4>
              <pre><code>fish_add_path ~/.cargo/bin</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="hint">Not sure which shell you use? Run <code>echo $SHELL</code> to find out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Initialize &amp; Set Up</h3>
          <p>Run the one-time setup wizard. This creates your encrypted data directory and walks you through configuring your LLM provider:</p>
          <pre><code>aivyx init</code></pre>
          <p class="hint">You'll be asked for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>🔑 <strong>API key</strong> — for OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini, or a local Ollama server</li>
            <li>🔒 <strong>Passphrase</strong> — encrypts all your data (never stored, only derived keys are kept)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">5</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Start Using Aivyx</h3>
          <p>You're ready! Pick your favourite way to interact:</p>
          <pre><code><span class="dim"># Quick single question</span>
aivyx run assistant "Explain ownership in Rust"

<span class="dim"># Interactive chat session</span>
aivyx chat assistant

<span class="dim"># Full terminal UI with sessions, markdown, vim keys</span>
aivyx tui assistant</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="verify-box">
        <h3>✓ Verify Everything Works</h3>
        <pre><code>$ aivyx --help
Secure, privacy-first AI agent framework

Commands:
  init       Initialize ~/.aivyx/
  run        Run a single-turn agent task
  chat       Interactive multi-turn chat
  tui        Launch the terminal UI
  ...</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="desktop-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>🖥️ Desktop App</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">A native graphical interface built with Tauri v2. Just download, install, and run — no terminal required.</p>

      <div class="download-grid">
        <div class="dl-card primary">
          <div class="dl-icon">🐧</div>
          <h3>Linux (AppImage)</h3>
          <p>Works on any Linux distro. No installation needed — just download, make executable, and run.</p>
          <a href="/releases/latest/aivyx-desktop.AppImage" class="btn btn-download">Download .AppImage</a>
          <pre><code><span class="dim"># Make it executable and run</span>
chmod +x aivyx-desktop.AppImage
./aivyx-desktop.AppImage</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-card">
          <div class="dl-icon">📦</div>
          <h3>Linux (.deb)</h3>
          <p>For Ubuntu, Debian, Pop!_OS, and other apt-based distros.</p>
          <a href="/releases/latest/aivyx-desktop.deb" class="btn btn-download">Download .deb</a>
          <pre><code><span class="dim"># Install with dpkg</span>
sudo dpkg -i aivyx-desktop.deb</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-card">
          <div class="dl-icon">💻</div>
          <h3>Linux (CLI Binary)</h3>
          <p>Pre-built CLI binary — no Rust compiler needed.</p>
          <a href="/releases/latest/aivyx-linux-x86_64.tar.gz" class="btn btn-download">Download CLI Tarball</a>
          <pre><code><span class="dim"># Extract and install</span>
tar xzf aivyx-linux-x86_64.tar.gz
sudo mv aivyx /usr/local/bin/
aivyx init</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="coming-soon">
        <h4>macOS &amp; Windows</h4>
        <p>Native .dmg (macOS) and .msi (Windows) packages are in development. For now, you can <a href="#cli">install from source using Cargo</a> on any platform.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="alt-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Alternative: Build from Source</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">For contributors who want the full repo.</p>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/AivyxDev/aivyx.git
cd aivyx
cargo build --release
./target/release/aivyx init</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="local-llm">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Want Fully Local AI?</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Use <a href="https://ollama.com" target="_blank">Ollama</a> for 100% offline inference — no API keys, no cloud, no data leaving your machine.</p>
      <pre><code><span class="dim"># Install Ollama (one command)</span>
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

<span class="dim"># Pull a model</span>
ollama pull llama3.2

<span class="dim"># Then tell Aivyx to use it</span>
aivyx config set provider ollama
aivyx config set ollama.model llama3.2</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="requirements">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>System Requirements</h2>
      <div class="req-grid">
        <div class="req-card">
          <h3>🐧 Linux</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>x86_64 or aarch64</li>
            <li>glibc 2.31+</li>
            <li>OpenSSL 3.x</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="req-card">
          <h3>🍎 macOS</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>macOS 12+ (Monterey)</li>
            <li>Apple Silicon or Intel</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="req-card">
          <h3>🪟 Windows</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Windows 10+</li>
            <li>x86_64</li>
            <li>Visual C++ Build Tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 2rem 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .accent { color: var(--accent); }
  .page-hero p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  .section-inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .section-sub {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .step-num {
    min-width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  .step-content { flex: 1; }
  .step-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .step-content p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .step-content ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .step-content li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.3rem 0;
  }
  .hint {
    font-size: 0.85rem !important;
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .tab-group {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .tab-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.75rem;
  }
  .tab-card h4 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .tab-card pre {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .verify-box {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(127, 176, 105, 0.3);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .verify-box h3 {
    color: var(--success);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .alt-section {
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .dim { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .req-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .req-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .req-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  .req-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .req-card li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .step { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .tab-group { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .req-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .download-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  /* Desktop Download Section */
  .desktop-section {
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .download-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .dl-card {
    background: var(--background);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .dl-card.primary {
    border-color: rgba(217, 175, 107, 0.4);
  }
  .dl-icon {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .dl-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .dl-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .dl-card pre {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .btn-download {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #1a1a1a;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    transition: opacity 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .btn-download:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .coming-soon {
    background: var(--background);
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .coming-soon h4 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .coming-soon p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
